OL,3,CReeves says Waspi compensation
OL,4,Cwouldn't be the 'best use of
OL,5,Ctaxpayers' money'
OL,7,FRachel Reeves says the government
OL,8,Fwon't pay "expensive compensation" for
OL,9,FWaspi women because it wouldn't "be
OL,10,Fthe best use of taxpayers' money."
OL,12,FThe Chancellor said she "understand(s)
OL,13,Fthat women affected by the changes to
OL,14,Fthe state pension age feel
OL,15,Fdisappointed by this decision", but
OL,16,F"the vast majority of people did know
OL,17,Fabout these changes."
